==English==
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pæn'en'thi'ĭz'əm}}

===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} ''[[πάν]]'' (pán) "all"; [[w:English|English]] [[en-]] (prefix form of in); and {{Gr.}} ''[[θεός]] (Theós) "god".

===Alternative spellings===
*sometimes hyphenated: '''pan-en-theism'''
*sometimes either the P or both the P and the initial T are capitalized: '''Panentheism''', '''PanenTheism'''
*variations of capitalization and spacing may be combined: '''Pan-en-theism''', '''Pan-en-Theism'''

===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|Panentheism}}
'''panentheism'''
# a [[philosophy]] that the [[universe]] is part of [[God]], but that God nevertheless transcends or has some existence separate from the universe
# a [[belief]] in all [[god]]s

